body: Hey @antonio-rylke-vgl, can you reproduce the issue on https://psalm.dev ?
Tried to reproduce on https://psalm.dev but it needs `\PHPUnit\Framework\TestCase`.
That's not a false-positive – that test will always fail: https://psalm.dev/r/60d5517050

@muglug 
The unit test does not fail, it succeeds. What do you mean by `that test will always fail`? Why should Psalm alert an error, i don't see the reason here?
Are you sure you’ve pasted the correct code? Asserting empty on an object will always fail
Oh sorry, didn’t see it’s countable
Doesn't it belong to [phpunit plugin repo](https://github.com/psalm/phpunit-psalm-plugin/issues) though?
No, this was an issue with how Psalm evaluates all `empty` assertions.

But `empty()` on objects always returns `false`, as you noted above. `implements Countable` makes no difference here: https://3v4l.org/XP4cd

So this: https://psalm.dev/r/32aecd92ff should still be flagged, but now it isn't.

@muglug 
`PHPUnit\Framework\Assert::assertIsEmpty()` is different though, as it explicitly checks for `$value instanceof Countable && count($value) === 0`
Ah thanks, I've now reverted those changes
I guess that's just an awkward bug then but, as you say, not a bug with Psalm.
